/* Sultan Choudhury */

AfD: Nominated for deletion; see [[Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Sultan Choudhury]]. The person is not notable for this article to remain. There is a clear lack of objectivity in the article e.g. Career and Early Life. The quoted sources for such sections are very poor and not independent as they could be paid for to provide a feature. What is the relation of pilgrimage here, it is a bit dramatic rather than objective facts. Also there is not an independent reliable source about his advisory

This person is not notable, very poor sources regarding his career and early life. There is a strong ground for the deletion of this article. He was sacked as a CEO of Al Rayan Bank due to serious issues, which was clear from the statement released by the bank employed him (see reference No. 1), the bank removed any connection with him anywherand is no longer active or has any notable activities that may give merits for keeping this article. Thus, we strongly recommend deletion of this article.

Not to mention claims that are not independently supported, such as advisory to government, career and early life sections. I support deleting this article ~~~~

* Delete*~~~~/* Sultan Choudhury */ (<includeonly>[[Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Sultan Choudhury]] I agree with the assessment provided above, the person is not notable and the article lacks a objectivity, reliable sources or compliance with Wiki's policies. While I would not make the assumption of paid media to conduct interviews or features, the points raised by {{U|Majidii1234}} are valid and reasonable. I fully support the deletion of this article.
